But the crash is still happening, which means either:
1. My fix is not being reached, or
2. The issue is not in `vectorizeGEPIndices` at all

Let me check if there are other places where GEPs are processed.

Looking at the stack trace again, it definitely shows `vectorizeGEPIndices` at line 21007.

Maybe the issue is that my fix is after some other processing that has already modified the candidates.

Let me move my fix earlier in the function.

Actually, let me look at the exact location where I inserted the fix. I inserted it right after `SetVector<Value *> Candidates(GEPList.begin(), GEPList.end());`.

But there's processing that happens before the bundle creation:

```cpp
// Some of the candidates may have already been vectorized after we
// initially collected them or their index is optimized to constant value.
// If so, they are marked as deleted, so remove them from the set of
// candidates.
Candidates.remove_if([&R](Value *I) {
  return R.isDeleted(cast<Instruction>(I)) ||
         isa<Constant>(cast<GetElementPtrInst>(I)->idx_begin()->get());
});

// Remove from the set of candidates all pairs of getelementptrs with
// constant differences. Such getelementptrs are likely not good
// candidates for vectorization in a bottom-up phase since one can be
// computed from the other. We also ensure all candidate getelementptr
// indices are unique.
for (int I = 0, E = GEPList.size(); I < E && Candidates.size() > 1; ++I) {
  auto *GEPI = GEPList[I];
  if (!Candidates.count(GEPI))
    continue;
  const SCEV *SCEVI = SE->getSCEV(GEPList[I]);
  for (int J = I + 1; J < E && Candidates.size() > 1; ++J) {
    auto *GEPJ = GEPList[J];
    const SCEV *SCEVJ = SE->getSCEV(GEPList[J]);
    if (isa<SCEVConstant>(SE->getMinusSCEV(SCEVI, SCEVJ))) {
      Candidates.remove(GEPI);
      Candidates.remove(GEPJ);
    } else if (GEPI->idx_begin()->get() == GEPJ->idx_begin()->get()) {
      Candidates.remove(GEPJ);
    }
  }
}

// We break out of the above computation as soon as we know there are
// fewer than two candidates remaining.
if (Candidates.size() < 2)
  continue;
```

My fix should be after this processing, because the candidate set might change.

Let me move my fix to after this processing:

```bash
# Remove the current fix
sed -i '/Check if all GEP indices that are instructions come from the same basic block/,+15d' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp

# Insert the fix after the existing candidate processing
sed -i '/if (Candidates.size() < 2)/a \
\
      // Check if all GEP indices that are instructions come from the same basic block.\n\
      BasicBlock *CommonBB = nullptr;\n\
      bool HasMultipleBBs = false;\n\
      for (auto *V : Candidates) {\n\
        auto *GEP = cast<GetElementPtrInst>(V);\n\
        auto *GEPIdx = GEP->idx_begin()->get();\n\
        auto *IdxInst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(GEPIdx);\n\
        if (!IdxInst) continue;\n\
        if (!CommonBB) {\n\
          CommonBB = IdxInst->getParent();\n\
        } else if (IdxInst->getParent() != CommonBB) {\n\
          HasMultipleBBs = true;\n\
          break;\n\
        }\n\
      }\n\
      if (HasMultipleBBs) {\n\
        continue;\n\
      }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp
```

